name: CRM-system-go-microservices
description: Customer Relationship Management helps to manage tasks, assign deadlines, control user roles, use of admin panel, feedback management, sales representation, deal management

name: CecoChat
description: Chat engine designed for millions of users. System design based on microservice architecture. Implementation based on cloud agnostic technologies. Configurable, observable, containerized and runnable, deployable local environment. Kafka, YugabyteDB, Cassandra, MinIO, HTTP, gRPC, Redis, .NET 8, ASP.NET, OpenTelemetry, Docker, Kubernetes.

name: mailing-list-microservice
description: A microservice-based mailing list management system using Go, gRPC, Docker, and SQLite. It offers both HTTP and gRPC APIs for managing email entries, containerized for easy deployment and scalability.

name: microservice
description: Welcome to the repository for my microservice project! This repository is dedicated to the implementation and testing of various microservices as part of my learning exercise in distributed systems and software architecture.

name: pos_dotnet_ex
description: Concept Point of Sale (POS) system - Blazor UI and Microservices, HTML, Frotnend

name: Distributed-Systems-Project
description: I created an application for an energy management system for the distributed systems laboratory using Java, Spring-Boot and Angular. The architecture used is based on microservices, the communication between them being realized with RabbitMq. Docker was used for deployment.

name: prefetch
description: A Scala based microservice that fetches and processes remote files. Part of the Document Library eco-system

name: API-Gateway
description: This project is an API Gateway developed in Go, designed to manage communication between microservices. The API Gateway includes features such as load balancing, rate limiting, authentication, and monitoring. It serves as a central entry point for clients to access various microservices within the system.

name: oms
description: group of microservices using gRPC and http for communication; written in Go; simulating an order management system with jwt auth

name: speller-simulation-prototype
description: A minimal working system prototype of microservices supporting a Speller worker built with several state-of-the-art software tools.

name: Travel_Agency
description: The project involves developing a modularized management system with three microservices in Java Spring Boot, connected to a database. These services include hotel, reservation, and flight management, with a frontend for user interaction.
